Binning by MT

General binning where we do not split by the type of modification:

df <- ptms_mt %>%
  mutate(mt_group = case_when(
    mean_mt <= 45 ~ "40-45",
    mean_mt <= 50 ~ "45-50",
    mean_mt <= 55 ~ "50-55",
    mean_mt <= 60 ~ "55-60",
    mean_mt <= 65 ~ "60-65",
    mean_mt <= 70 ~ "65-70",
    TRUE ~ "70+"
  )) 

mean_counts_per_mt_group <- df %>%
  group_by(Uniprot_entry_name) %>%
  summarize(sum_ptms = sum(counts_norm_abund_len), mt_group) %>% 
  distinct() %>% group_by(mt_group) %>% summarise(mean_ptms_group = mean(sum_ptms))
Warning: Returning more (or less) than 1 row per `summarise()` group was deprecated in
dplyr 1.1.0.
â¹ Please use `reframe()` instead.
â¹ When switching from `summarise()` to `reframe()`, remember that `reframe()`
  always returns an ungrouped data frame and adjust accordingly.
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'Uniprot_entry_name'. You can override
using the `.groups` argument.
# Plot bar chart
ggplot(mean_counts_per_mt_group, aes(x = mt_group, y = mean_ptms_group)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = 'dodge') +
  scale_x_discrete(limits = c("40-45", "45-50", "50-55", "55-60", "60-65", "65-70")) +
  labs(x = "Melting temperature (Â°C)",
       y = "Mean normalised counts") +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(),
        legend.text = element_text(size = 16, family = "Lato"),
        legend.position = c(0.8,0.92),
